<h2>Jack of All Trades</h2>

<p><strong>Class:</strong> Multiclass progression through nearly every class</p>
<p><strong>Race:</strong> Duergar (recommended for invisibility) or Githyanki (for mobility)</p>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> Flexible — prioritize dialogue skills</p>

<h3>Stats</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Strength:</strong> 8</li>
    <li><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 16 (14 + 2)</li>
    <li><strong>Constitution:</strong> 16 (14 + 2)</li>
    <li><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 8 (boosted to 17 via Circlet of Intelligence)</li>
    <li><strong>Wisdom:</strong> 12</li>
    <li><strong>Charisma:</strong> 14</li>
</ul>

<h3>Build Summary</h3>
<p>
    This build is designed for the <strong>Jack of All Trades achievement</strong> and Honour Mode survival. It prioritizes utility, dialogue options, and survivability over raw damage. By taking one level in nearly every class, you gain access to a wide toolkit of spells, skills, and abilities while still maintaining strong Constitution and Dexterity for defense.
</p>

<h3>Character Progression</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Level 1:</strong> Sorcerer (Storm Sorcerer) — Constitution proficiency, charisma dialogue options, Magic Missile, Shield. Cantrips: Friends, Mage Hand, Minor Illusion, plus one free choice.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 2:</strong> Cleric (Light Domain) — Warding Flare, Bless, Sanctuary. Cantrips: Guidance, Thaumaturgy, Resistance.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 3:</strong> Bard — Cantrips: Dancing Lights, True Strike. Spells: Disguise Self, Healing Word, Longstrider, Speak with Animals.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 4:</strong> Wizard — Pick up Warped Headband. Cantrips: Blade Ward, Firebolt, Acid Splash. Spells: Find Familiar, Feather Fall, False Life, Enhanced Leap, Fog Cloud, Grease.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 5:</strong> Druid — Cantrips: Shillelagh, Vine Whip. Spells: Goodberry, Create Water. Grants 3rd-level spell slots.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 6:</strong> Rogue — Skill proficiencies (e.g., Sleight of Hand).</li>
    <li><strong>Level 7:</strong> Fighter — Second Wind. Fighting Style: Protection (party utility) or Defense.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 8:</strong> Ranger — Favored Enemy: Ranger Knight (heavy armor). Natural Explorer: Wasteland Wanderer (Fire or Cold).</li>
    <li><strong>Level 9:</strong> Warlock — Booming Blade.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 10:</strong> Barbarian — Extra hit points.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 11:</strong> Monk — Minimal benefit, but required for achievement.</li>
    <li><strong>Level 12:</strong> Paladin — Oath of the Crown recommended for utility. Avoid breaking oath to preserve achievement.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Key Gear</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Warped Headband:</strong> Sets Intelligence to 17 for Wizard spells.</li>
    <li><strong>Dwarven Splintmail:</strong> 19 AC, reduces piercing damage, +1 Strength saves/checks, +2 Constitution (up to 20).</li>
    <li><strong>Sentinel Shield:</strong> Improved initiative.</li>
    <li><strong>Phalar Aluve:</strong> Utility weapon.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Playstyle Tips</h3>
<p>
    This build is about versatility and survival. Use Duergar invisibility or Githyanki mobility to avoid unnecessary fights and position strategically. Lean on utility spells like Bless, Sanctuary, Healing Word, and Goodberry to support your party. With access to nearly every class toolkit, you can adapt to any situation in Honour Mode while ensuring you unlock the achievement.
</p>